The paper presents a robotic system that autonomously manipulates objects in warehouse scenarios, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The system uses perception methods to detect and estimate the pose of objects, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The system also uses grasp planning and decision-making algorithms, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the system operates in a dynamic environment and requires control and coordination, which are related to systems and control (cs.SY).
